 44→// Suppress Vite's CSS preload errors in the Chrome extension content script context.
 45→// Dynamic imports (e.g., mermaid) trigger Vite's __vitePreload helper which tries to
 46→// create <link> elements with paths like "/assets/foo.css". In a content script, these
 47→// resolve to the web page origin (e.g., https://gemini.google.com/assets/foo.css)
 48→// instead of the extension, causing false "Unable to preload CSS" errors.
 49→// The CSS is already injected via contentStyle.css, so these preloads are unnecessary.
 50→window.addEventListener('vite:preloadError', (event) => {
 51→  event.preventDefault();
 52→});
